sub_title: Bilingual journalist in the rail industry
summary:
I've always had a fascination for culture, and curiosity regarding what it means to be from somewhere. As a young person concerned by the global rise of populism, I developed a keen interest in politics and international relations, but also communication and media. Indeed, I believe that media plays a key role in fostering mutual understanding between diverse communities. Entering the workforce in the age of â€˜fake newsâ€™ and â€˜infodemicsâ€™, I consider journalism a public good. I am passionate about using my love of research and writing, to contribute to a better informed and connected world.

TCK | Idealist | Zillenial
